Here's a clean implementation using `CommunityToolkit.Mvvm` (the recommended approach for .NET MAUI):

```csharp
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.ComponentModel;
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.Input;

namespace YourApp.ViewModels;

public partial class ProductDetailViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _name = string.Empty;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private decimal _price;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isAvailable;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isLoading;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task LoadAsync()
    {
        IsLoading = true;
        try
        {
            // Replace with your actual data service call
            await Task.Delay(500);

            Name = "Widget Pro";
            Price = 29.99m;
            IsAvailable = true;
        }
        finally
        {
            IsLoading = false;
        }
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

- `[ObservableProperty]` source-generates the public property + `OnPropertyChanged` call from the backing field (e.g., `_name` → `Name`).
- `[RelayCommand]` generates `LoadCommand` (an `IAsyncRelayCommand`) from `LoadAsync()`. It automatically disables while running.
- The class must be `partial` for the source generators to work.
- Add the NuGet package: `dotnet add package CommunityToolkit.Mvvm`

**Binding in XAML:**

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels">
    <ContentPage.BindingContext>
        <vm:ProductDetailViewModel />
    </ContentPage.BindingContext>

    <VerticalStackLayout Padding="16">
        <Label Text="{Binding Name}" FontSize="24" />
        <Label Text="{Binding Price, StringFormat='{0:C}'}" />
        <Label Text="{Binding IsAvailable, Converter={StaticResource BoolToStockConverter}}" />
        <Button Text="Load" Command="{Binding LoadCommand}" />
        <ActivityIndicator IsRunning="{Binding IsLoading}" IsVisible="{Binding IsLoading}" />
    </VerticalStackLayout>
</ContentPage>
```
